<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - INSPECTION AND REPAIR - CRANKSHAFT GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CRANKSHAFT GEAR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <para>Replace the crankshaft gear as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a chisel between the gear teeth and strike the chisel with a hammer to split the
                    gear.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil pump drive spline first to access the crankshaft gear. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050742">7.42</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Be careful not to damage the crankshaft during gear removal.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With gears removed, heat the crankshaft gear and oil pump drive spline to 370-395&#176;
                    F (188-202&#176; C).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the crankshaft gear first. Be sure the locating pin on the crankshaft gear
                    aligns with the crankshaft properly. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050743">7.43</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Press the gear into place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the hot oil pump drive spline onto the crankshaft until flush with the
                    crankshaft gear. See
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050743">7.43</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050742" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3057" filename="../figeg3/EG3057.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.42.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Hammer</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Chisel</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Crankshaft</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050743" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12182" filename="../figcg1/CG12182.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.43.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
